/-!
# Ordered swap resolution over the universal polynomial-orbit history grid

The universal arbitrary-multiplicity envelope is indexed by an ordered square
grid of retained raw-history occurrences.  This file packages the guarded local
swap law uniformly over that grid.  It deliberately does not reorder the matrix
product or identify the conservative envelope with a global Hall schedule.

The remaining arbitrary-cutoff input is exposed as an inventory of genuinely
nonterminal recursive swap kernels.  Through cutoff three that inventory, and
therefore the complete grid-cell swap package, is unconditional.

This file is intentionally not imported by the existing collection proof.
-/

noncomputable section

namespace Towers
