/-!
# Retained-transversal finite traces at arbitrary cutoff

The retained closure transversal exists at every cutoff and has a
well-founded decomposition by smaller selected parent recipes.  Its global
ordered product identity is not automatic: that is the remaining symbolic
recollection theorem.

This file encodes the transversal as one fixed finite polynomial-orbit trace
and proves that its all-integral trace law is exactly the retained
recipe-product theorem.  Consequently, the same theorem is equivalent to an
order-aware alignment with every collected natural endpoint together with the
signed lift of that alignment.

No global recollection identity is assumed silently, and no permutation or
deduplication argument is used.

This file is intentionally not imported by the existing collection proof.
-/

noncomputable section

namespace Towers
namespace TCTex
namespace
  ERTransv

universe u

open
  CSAggreg
open
  CTAssigna
open
  CCThree
open
  RITrace
open
  ECThree
