/-!
# Recursive provenance for the retained-transversal symbolic trace

The retained-transversal finite trace is occurrence preserving.  This file
keeps that order visible while attaching each decoded symbolic factor to the
selected retained recipe at the same position.  The certificate records its
substituted word, its evaluation for every exponent family, and the
source-or-strictly-smaller-selected-parents branch of the retained recipe.

At root-weight symbolic parents, the recipe-weight descent becomes literal
Hall-word-weight descent inside the decoded symbolic factor list.  This yields
a factor-level well-founded induction principle suitable for a future
symbolic collector.

This file is intentionally not imported by the existing collection proof.
-/

noncomputable section

namespace Towers
namespace TCTex
namespace
  SRProven

universe u v w x

open HACoeff
open ROEvalua
open ROAggreg
open BRSpec
open
  CFSubsti
open
  CTAssigna
open
  RITrace
open
  ECThree
